- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper uses dynamic models to analyze the spread of information. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper uses systems of ordinary differential equations to model the spread of information. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper applies mathematical models to analyze a real-world problem related to infectious diseases. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on developing new algorithms or data structures, but rather on applying existing models to analyze data.
